THE AREA IS INTENSIVELY FARMED.THE FARMS TEND TO BE LARGE AND MAINLY DEVOTED TO ARABLE CROPS.THE MAJOR CROP IS {SUGAR BEET }WHICH IS SENT TO BE PROCESSED AT B.S.C. FACTORIES IN {BURY {ST.EDMUNDS.}
OTHER CROPS GROWN INCLUDE{BARLEY,CORN, {SWEET CORN,OIL SEED RAPE}AND {APARAGUS. SWEET CORN }HAS GROWN RAPIDLY AS AN IMPORTANT CROP.{ SOME OF THE AREA FARMS HAVE ROUGH PASTURE WHERE COWS AND SHEEP ARE GRAZED.SOME PIGS ARE REARED.
THERE IS SOME CONTROVERSY IN THE AREA ABOUT THE PRACTICE OF SOME FARMS REMOVING HEDGEROWS TO INCREASE THE EFFICENCY OF THE FARM.SOME FARMERS ARE ACTIVELY TRYING TO RESTORE THE BALENCE BY PLANTING NEW HEDGEROWS AND TREES.
